article.headline: Old Dominion 64, William &amp, Mary 63
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Frank Hassell and Ben Finney scored 13 points each and Old Dominion held off William & Mary 64-63 on Wednesday night. The Monarchs (19-9, 11-6 Colonial Athletic Association) led 49-40 with 10:02 left, but the Tribe rallied to tie the game at 53. William & Mary pulled ahead 61-58 with 1:38 remaining, but Darius James hit a 3-pointer to tie the game for the 12th time. Jonathan Adams added a 3 for Old Dominion with 36 seconds remaining for a 64-61 lead. Danny Sumner then hit a jumper to pull the Tribe (9-19, 4-13) within one point with 11 seconds left. After a missed shot by William & Mary's Quinn McDowell, James missed a free throw with nine seconds on the clock. David Schneider, who led the Tribe with 22 points, got the rebound, but missed a 3-point attempt and the Monarchs won their fourth straight game and eighth of their last nine.
